                                      RM_PARAM flags to SPINRISE config
                                      names with recommended defaults —
                                      <b>this is the best parameter
                                        documentation of any module so
                                        far and is exactly what the v2
                                        guide requires.<br>
                                      </b><br>
                                      The 7 critical defects are clearly
                                      documented with SPINRISE actions.
                                      CD-2 (MAX+1 race condition), CD-3
                                      (PR balance without UPDLOCK), and
                                      CD-4 (RM_DELSCHED without primary
                                      key) are important architectural
                                      defects that the SPINRISE
                                      development team must address.
                                      CD-7 (DelReason not written to DB)
                                      is correctly flagged as requiring
                                      IST confirmation before the fix
                                      can be specified.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>On the PM's feedback — what
                                        needs correction before Sasi
                                        acts</b><br>
                                      <br>
                                      Saravanan, I want to clarify
                                      several points in your feedback
                                      before Sasi revises the document.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>First, on tooling:</b> your
                                      feedback is marked as ChatGPT
                                      feedback. The SPINRISE FSD review
                                      process uses Claude AI throughout
                                      — for documentation, analysis, and
                                      review at every level of the
                                      review chain. Please ensure that
                                      your IST reviews going forward are
                                      conducted using Claude AI,
                                      consistent with the rest of the
                                      team. This applies to the PM level
                                      as well.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>Second, some of your Must Fix
                                        items are already in the
                                        document:</b><br>
                                      <br>
                                      The PO number generation race
                                      condition is already documented as
                                      CD-2 in Section 5.4 and Section
                                      12.1, with the correct SPINRISE
                                      fix (locked sequence table with
                                      UPDLOCK) already specified. <b>This
                                        does not need to be added — it
                                        is there.</b><br>
                                      <br>
                                      The Delete Reason storage question
                                      is already in the document as CD-7
                                      in Section 5.10 and as IST-8 in
                                      Section 13, both marked as pending
                                      IST confirmation. The developer
                                      has correctly flagged that the
                                      code captures the value but no DB
                                      write is observable. IST-8 is your
                                      question to answer as the M02 IST
                                      member — not something for Sasi to
                                      add a note about.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>Third, two of your Important
                                        Improvement items are also
                                        already in the document:<br>
                                      </b><br>
                                      With-Sample mode is fully
                                      documented in Section 5.8,
                                      including the wosample flag, both
                                      modes (With-Sample vs
                                      Rate-Master), and the difference
                                      in GST auto-fill behaviour between
                                      the two. Please read Section 5.8.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      The Season field difference
                                      between Add and Modify is
                                      documented in Section 5.9 and in
                                      Section 3's field rules table.
                                      This is already done.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <b>Fourth, HV-17 and HV-18 are not
                                        duplicate validations. </b>They
                                      are mirror-image checks — HV-17
                                      fires on LostFocus of the From
                                      field (From must be less than or
                                      equal to To), and HV-18 fires on
                                      LostFocus of the To field (To must
                                      be greater than or equal to From).
                                      Both are needed at their
                                      respective field events and
                                      merging them would reduce
                                      validation coverage, not improve
                                      it.<br>
                                      <br>
                                      <br>
